D

Demo_CalypsoBasicTransactionEngine - Class in org.eclipse.keyple.example.common.calypso
This Calypso demonstration code consists in: Setting up a two-reader configuration and adding an observer method (update) Starting a card operation when a PO presence is notified (operatePoTransactions) Opening a logical channel with the CSM (C1 CSM is expected) see (CSM_C1_ATR_REGEX) Attempting to open a logical channel with the PO with 3 options: Selection with a fake AID Selection with a Navigo AID Selection with a Hoplink AID Display SeRequest/SeResponse data (printSelectAppResponseStatus) If the Calypso selection succeeded, do a Calypso transaction (Demo_CalypsoBasicTransactionEngine.doCalypsoReadWriteTransaction(PoSecureSession, ApduResponse, boolean) doCalypsoReadWriteTransaction}).
Demo_CalypsoBasicTransactionEngine() - Constructor for class org.eclipse.keyple.example.common.calypso.Demo_CalypsoBasicTransactionEngine

This Calypso demonstration code consists in: Setting up a two-reader configuration and adding an observer method (update) Starting a card operation when a PO presence is notified (operatePoTransactions) Opening a logical channel with the CSM (C1 CSM is expected) see (CSM_C1_ATR_REGEX) Attempting to open a logical channel with the PO with 3 options: Selection with a fake AID Selection with a Navigo AID Selection with a Hoplink AID Display SeRequest/SeResponse data (printSelectAppResponseStatus) If the Hoplink selection succeeded, do an Hoplink transaction (Demo_HoplinkTransactionEngine.doHoplinkReadWriteTransaction(PoSecureSession, ApduResponse, boolean) doHoplinkReadWriteTransaction}).
